This paper discusses the reorganization of the journalistic discourse considering the materialization of an active reading process on digital journalism, from hypertext. We consider also the implications of the discursive function while reading the discourse, which is stated in a dialogical movement to give meaning to a text. Starting with a brief overview of the readerâ€™s position in the journalistic text construction dialectic and considering the inclusion of new language derived from hypertextual programming logic, it aims to discuss the forms of manifestation of reading activities, the structure protruding digital journalism.